extract pyMathBitPrecise, pycocotb, rm Params as const. signals

* Bits type was extracted to pyMathBitPrecise
* HBool an HInt were replaced by parametrized Bits instance
* type conversion between equivalent types is permissive, this means
  that boolean to std_logic conversions in vhdl have to be generated
  by serializer
* Param class does not inherit from signal any more. Now it is only
  marker which stores the name of the property and parent object
  for value. After parameter is added to Unit instance the value
  of parameter is present in property and Param object is stored only
  in ._params
  This means that constant parameter expressions does not exists anymore
  because the Param can not be used in HDL expression and value
  is used instead
* Verif. agents <-> HdlSimulator API has been reworked,
  so the simulations with multiple scenarios does not have to always
  compile the simulator. This is required for Verilator and oters.
* The system of simulator triggers were reworked to be more cocotb-like.
